{"article_id":"8vZ3HK7zjyUNTSqE","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Wednesday morning , at 10 o'clock , students at schools across the country will walk out of their classrooms .","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"The plan is for them to leave school","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"- or at least gather in the hallway -","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"for 17 minutes .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"That 's one minute for each of the victims in last month 's school shooting in Parkland , Fla .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"The walkout has galvanized teens nationwide","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"and raised big questions for schools","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"about how to handle protests .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"The organizers , Women 's March Youth EMPOWER , have made it clear :","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"While this walkout is meant to honor the victims in Parkland , as well as anyone","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"who 's experienced gun violence ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"it is also a political call to action .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"`` It 's about protesting Congress ' inaction","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"when it comes to gun violence , ''","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"says Kaleab Jegol , a 17-year-old high school senior and protest coordinator from Ohio .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"Organizers have posted their demands online ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"including an assault weapons ban and expanded background checks .","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"Jegol knows ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"their protest is n't sitting well with some school leaders .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"In Needville , Texas , Superintendent Curtis Rhodes issued a stern warning to students and parents :","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Texas - A letter","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"sent to families by Needville ISD Superintendent Curtis Rhodes ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"threatens students with a three-day , out-of-school suspension","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"if they join in growing protests nationwide over the Florida shooting.","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"https : //t.co/pZaBWZ6FIj","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"# NeverAgain # MarchForOurLives","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"pic.twitter.com/vTnKR6EQJ","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"1 - Antonio Arellano","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"( @ AntonioArellano )","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"February 21 , 2018","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Needville High School 's Facebook page ,","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"where the letter was posted ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"has since been taken down .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"Rhodes did not respond to an interview request ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"but the district tells NPR","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"that it stands by its suspension threat .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"This is why ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Jegol says ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"students need to know their rights .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"`` If it 's possible to work with [ your school 's ] administration ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"then great , ''","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"Jegol says .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"``","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"if consequences like suspension are being threatened ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"students still do have those First Amendment rights . ''","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Turns out , this walkout is a fascinating walk - out onto a tightrope ,","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"stretched between students ' free speech rights and schools ' legal obligations .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"And like any tightrope , this one 's full of tension .","depth":4},{"id":49,"text":"`` It can hardly be argued that either students or teachers shed their constitutional rights to freedom of speech or expression at the schoolhouse gate . ''","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"So wrote a 7-2 majority of the U.S. Supreme Court in 1969 ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"after hearing the case of Mary Beth Tinker .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"The Des Moines teenager had worn a black armband to school , in protest of the Vietnam War ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"and school leaders suspended her for it .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"The Court sided with Tinker","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"because ,","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"the justices reasoned ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"her protest did not `` materially and substantially disrupt the work and discipline of the school . '' A walkout , though , is no armband ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"and likely exceeds students ' free speech protections .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"`` Is [ the demonstration ] going to be disruptive to the learning and educational mission of the school ? ''","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"asks Esha Bhandari , a staff attorney with the American Civil Liberties Union .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"If so ,","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Bhandari says ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"then schools are within their rights","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"to intervene","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"and even punish students .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Some schools have promised not to punish students","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"who walk out .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Others have said","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"the walkout will be considered an unexcused absence","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"and punished accordingly , usually gently .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"For schools like those in Needville ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"that have promised harsher punishment ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"Bhandari has a warning :","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"`` Students should n't be punished any differently","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"than any other unexplained or unexcused absence would be .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"I think","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"that 's the really critical distinction here . ''","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"It all comes down to pre-existing district policy .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"If the student code of conduct says","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"skipping class should trigger a note home or detention ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"then school leaders ca n't start handing out three-day suspensions .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"If they do ,","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"it could be argued ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"they 're punishing students for their political speech , not for their actions .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"We 'll be a little reductive here ,","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"but it 's worth mapping out schools ' basic options in response to the walkout .","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"And you 'll see ,","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"there are no basic options .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"Instead of attempting to shut down the walkout","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"before it starts","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"with threats of harsh punishment ,","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"principals could head in the opposite direction ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"just letting students walk .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"But , that 's complicated , too .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"`` Schools stand in what 's known as loco parentis ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"so we do n't simply release our students into the ether , ''","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"says Francisco Negron , Chief Legal Officer at the National School Boards Association .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"`` In loco parentis '' is a legal term ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"and it means","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"schools are legally obligated to safeguard students .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"The irony is that this walkout is all about keeping students safe ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"but that 's also why school leaders do n't want to let them walk out .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Negron recently sent guidance to districts","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"to help them walk this tightrope .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Instead , many districts have said","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"they 'll allow the walkout","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"- but only for students","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"whose parents sign them out","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"or sign a permission slip .","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"In an effort","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"to keep students inside ,","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"some schools have talked about trying to turn the walkout into an assembly ,","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"to give protesters a safe forum .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"But Negron warns","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"that even this can be tricky :","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"`` When you open up a forum","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"for protests to happen ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"then you open up the possibility","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"that those parties","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"that you do n't allow in","depth":15},{"id":121,"text":"could claim","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"that you 're discriminating on the basis of viewpoint . ''","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"That 's why ,","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"when administrators in Gwinnett County , Ga. , announced","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"that they could not condone a student walkout ,","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"they spelled out why :","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"enforcing school rules for some protests but not others is grounds for a First Amendment violation .","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"Some schools have tried to protect themselves from such a charge of discrimination","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"by arguing","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"that the walkout or assembly","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"they 've sanctioned","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"is an apolitical event","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"meant to commemorate the victims in the Parkland shooting .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"The problem is ,","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"as we 've said ,","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"many students and organizers have been clear","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"that they believe","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"the walkout is and should be considered a political protest .","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"Perhaps the best plan for schools is also the most complicated - and creative .","depth":4},{"id":140,"text":"Administrators in Wallingford , Conn. , have offered students there a variety of alternatives to the walkout ,","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"including time","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"to write letters to their representatives","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"or complete homework in study hall .","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"Thirty minutes north , in Hartford , Conn. , `` Staff , administration , and students will be walking out , down to our football field ,","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"and we will stand there in silence for 17 minutes , ''","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"says Gage Salicki ,","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"who teaches social studies at Bulkeley High School .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"So the walkout will happen at Bulkeley ,","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"but that 's only half the story .","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"`` In preparation for this walkout , we asked","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"that students design something","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"related to civic action , ''","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"Salicki says .","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"In fact , Salicki helped build a multi-day lesson plan around the walkout","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"- one","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"he began teaching last week .","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"His class watched cell phone footage","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"taken by students during the shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"and explored all sides of America 's raging gun debate .","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"`` We wanted to make sure","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"that students ,","depth":15},{"id":162,"text":"if delving into some heavy legal territory","depth":16},{"id":163,"text":"related to Second Amendment rights ,","depth":16},{"id":164,"text":"would have equal access to the pros and cons of the issue , ''","depth":14},{"id":165,"text":"Salicki says .","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"The school 's approach was n't to shy away from politics","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"but to give students a range of resources","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"and encourage them to think critically about the facts .","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"Students were then asked to do one of a few things :","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"make a poster","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"to carry during the walkout ,","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"write a letter to a person in power","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"or write a song or poem about what they 've learned .","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"Salicki hopes","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"they 've turned this tension-filled moment into a teachable moment .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":351,"left":221,"right":350,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":183,"right":220,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":183,"left":180,"right":182,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":0,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":178,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":177,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":177,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":182,"left":5,"right":181,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":181,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":189,"right":219,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":186,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":8,"right":185,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":185,"left":184,"right":11,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":184,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":187,"right":14,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":203,"right":218,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":203,"left":190,"right":202,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":190,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":191,"right":201,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":201,"left":198,"right":200,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":198,"left":19,"right":197,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":197,"left":194,"right":196,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":192,"right":193,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":192,"left":20,"right":21,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":24,"right":195,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":195,"left":25,"right":26,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":200,"left":199,"right":29,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":199,"left":27,"right":28,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":205,"right":217,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":205,"left":204,"right":32,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":204,"left":30,"right":31,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":217,"left":210,"right":216,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":207,"right":209,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":207,"left":33,"right":206,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":206,"left":34,"right":35,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":209,"left":208,"right":38,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":208,